  RFC7214 [label="RFC7214
Moving Generic Associated Channel
(G-ACh) IANA Registries to a New
Registry
2014", shape=ellipse, fillcolor="#e8f0ff", tooltip="RFC 5586 generalized the applicability of the pseudowire Associated Channel Header (PW-ACH) into the Generic Associated Channel G-ACh. However, registries and allocations of G-ACh parameters had been distributed throughout different, sometimes unrelated, registries. This document coalesces these into a new Generic Associated Channel (G-ACh) Parameters registry under the Multiprotocol Label Switching Architecture (MPLS) heading. This document updates RFC 5586. This document also updates RFCs 6374, 6378, 6427, and 6428."]; 

